# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIREMENT DERIVATION RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Source Citation Standards

When deriving requirements from source documents:

1. **Always quote source text verbatim**
   - Use italics for quoted text
   - Preserve exact wording (including Arabic text when relevant)
   - Do NOT paraphrase unless explicitly noted

2. **Include precise location references**
   - Format: "ARA-BI-001, Tab X, Row Y, Column Z (Lines N-M in extracted MD)"
   - Include line numbers from machine-readable extraction
   - Reference cell references for Excel sources

3. **Handle Arabic text properly**
   - Include both Arabic original and English translation
   - Mark translations explicitly: "[Translation: ...]"
   - Note any transliteration conventions used

## Citation Format (LaTeX)

```latex
\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=sourcegreen!5,colframe=sourcegreen!70,title=Source Quotation]
\textit{``Exact quoted text from source document...''}

\textbf{Arabic Original:} \textarabic{النص العربي الأصلي}
\end{tcolorbox}

\begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{@{}lX@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Attribute} & \textbf{Value} \\
\midrule
\textbf{Requirement ID} & ARA-REQ-XXnn \\
\textbf{MoSCoW Priority} & MUST/SHOULD/COULD/WON'T \\
\textbf{Source Document} & Full document name \\
\textbf{Source ID} & ARA-BI-001/ARA-DOI-001/etc. \\
\textbf{Source Location} & Tab, Row, Column (Lines) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabularx}
```

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPEC-DRIFT SYNCHRONIZATION RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Critical Sync Points

1. **Requirements → Technical Spec**
   - Arabic-HITL requirements ↔ Arabic spec implementation
   - New requirements need corresponding technical design

2. **Requirements → Schema**
   - Acceptance criteria ↔ Schema validation rules
   - Field requirements must be in both spec and schema

3. **Requirements → Test Cases**
   - Acceptance criteria → Test implementations
   - Every AC-* must have corresponding test

## Pre-Change Checklist

Before modifying this specification:

- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=arabic`
- [ ] Check source document is still current
- [ ] Verify requirement doesn't conflict with existing ones
- [ ] Confirm acceptance criteria are measurable

## Post-Change Checklist

After modifying this specification:

- [ ] Update traceability matrix (Chapter 10)
- [ ] Update related Arabic technical spec if needed
- [ ] Update schemas if data requirements changed
- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift` to verify synchronization

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIREMENT ID CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Extraction | ARA-REQ-EXT | ARA-REQ-EXT01 |
| HITL Workflow | ARA-REQ-HITL | ARA-REQ-HITL01 |
| Quality | ARA-REQ-QA | ARA-REQ-QA01 |
| Integration | ARA-REQ-INT | ARA-REQ-INT01 |

## Acceptance Criteria IDs

Format: `AC-<REQ-ID>-<NUMBER>`

Example: `AC-EXT01-1`, `AC-HITL02-1`, `AC-QA01-2`

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MoSCoW PRIORITIZATION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Priority | Definition | v1.0 Impact |
|----------|------------|-------------|
| **MUST** | Non-negotiable for v1.0 | Blocks release |
| **SHOULD** | Important but can slip | Creates tech debt |
| **COULD** | Nice to have | Deferred to v1.1 |
| **WON'T** | Explicitly out of scope | Documented exclusion |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ARABIC-SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## RTL Processing Requirements

All Arabic-HITL requirements MUST consider:
- Right-to-left text direction handling
- Mixed Arabic/English content alignment
- Unicode normalization (NFC vs NFD)
- Font requirements for Arabic rendering

## Invoice Field Mapping

| English Field | Arabic Label | Validation Rule |
|---------------|--------------|-----------------|
| Invoice Number | رقم الفاتورة | Required, alphanumeric |
| Amount | المبلغ | Required, numeric > 0 |
| Date | التاريخ | Required, valid date |
| Vendor Name | اسم المورد | Required, text |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRIFT DETECTION COMMANDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

```bash
# Full audit for arabic domain (includes arabic-hitl)
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=arabic

# Check source document currency
ls -la docs/arabic/machine-readable/

# Verify requirement coverage
grep -c "ARA-REQ-" docs/latex/specs/arabic-hitl/chapters/*.tex
```

